            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "FYI as seen in my linked issue above for a neovim plugin (https://github.com/olimorris/codecompanion.nvim/issues/722) I am having problems with vim.filetype.match() as well specifically for TypeScript (`*.ts`) files. `js` and `tsx` files work fine, but `*.ts` files always return `nil` even when trying to add the content with it as well.\n\nSee simple repro (note, I am on Windows):\n\n```lua\nlua vim.notify(vim.inspect(vim.filetype.match({ filename = 'testing.ts' })))\nlua vim.notify(vim.inspect(vim.filetype.match({ filename = 'testing.js' })))\nlua vim.notify(vim.inspect(vim.filetype.match({ filename = 'testing.tsx' })))\n```\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9ecaba5b-6ab1-42d8-b37e-0f408cdf61a6)",
